content.detailedDescription:
1) my girlfriend and i were driving on highway 167 passing through auburn/kent area.

2) we were looking at the very dark rain clouds in the sky hoping it wouldn't rain on our camping trip to deception pass state park.

3)we knew it wasn't an airplane because it didn't have any wings or lights. we are very sure it was a disk. like a thick pancake shape.

4) the object was stationary (hovering) and then faded away.

5) we were floored by what we just saw and discussed it between ourselves to make sure our eyes weren't playing tricks on us. we ended up getting off at the next exit and sat in a parking lot with a camera in hand to snap a picture but it was already gone.

6) the object just faded away, but we are not sure if it dissolved or slipped into the cloud.





my girlfriend and i saw a pancake shaped object hovering in front of a dark cloud formation over the northeastern sky. it happened at 11:44 am as we were passing through auburn/ kent on highway 167. the entire event lasted no more than 2 minutes. it was a dull silvery color and appeared to be about the same length as a commercial airplane or maybe shorter. we are positive that it was not an airplane because it had no wings and we saw 2 airplanes flying by at the same time while we were staring at the object.
content.summary: Pancake shaped object hovering in northeastern sky in auburn/kent area while driving on highway 167.

content.detailedDescription: We were driving home talking. there were 3 of us and we spotted 3 glowing lights in the sky in a triangle formation at first stayed still then slowly moved together uniformly into on light formation like a star. then a 4 th glowing light started to head towards the other light and came together and then it disappeared. the lights in the sky was the first thing i saw. i thought at first it was a light tower. my feeling was excitement but also a sense of calm feeling. it was a amazing event to witness and thought that we were suppose to see those lights. we sat and waited to see if they would come back and nothing. it was quiet and silent. no sounds of airplanes. the objects disappeared after that all came together like a flame that was put out. there were 4 lighted objects total.
content.summary: 3 lights in a triangular formation at the same distance coming together at the same time and then a 4th light observed going towards the 3 that came together and disappeared.

content.detailedDescription: I just left work in bristol travelling  home at about 0410 when i saw a bright light in the sky to our right at first i thought it was a police helicopter hovering looking for someone, as we got closer to the end of the bypass to go on to the m4 (west) we noticed it was still on our right  like it was matching our speed. it was just there  in the sky i started to think it was the north star which would make sense,  any way we left the m4 and joined the m5 north and again this bright white light was still on our right when it should of been in front of us if it was the north star.  we just forgot about it until we got back to our home town, anyway  one of the guys wanted to go through the drive through to get some food when i noticed this light again and thought i would take a couple of photos of this bright star thingy while i looked at the photo we noticed  two other lights that we couldn't  see so i took another picture  and again there it was but this time it had a kind of a triangle  shape with vertical lines on which  remind me of vents. i felt kind of scared because the day before i saw a phil schyder  seminar(on the internet)  and said i wish i could see something like this and get some kind if proof  then boom! the day later this happens like "it" knew what i was thinking and it made me feel scared of  what i might if got myself in to so i thought i would fill in a report and just forget about it. i went home told the misses who said i should report to you guys because you know more about it than me and could possibly  been seen and reported by someone else.
content.summary: White object in sky like a star but brighter. one with pattern on side.

content.detailedDescription: i was on my way to my postal route in the east hollwood area around 9:30 am, coming down a hill in traffic at a stop sign, i looked up and classic saucer shaped object. the first thing i did was step out of the jeep and looked for wigs vertical stabilizer, engine nacelles windows, exhaust , i saw none. i observed till it disappeared over the griffith park hills. when i was delivering mail one of my customers a movie director said, did you see that strane thing in the sky this morning and i told him i did. latter that day upon returning to my station another postal carrier who at the time of oberving this ufo was a mile from me, also said did you see that strange thing in the sky this morning(this employee was in the aqi force at one time and part of a refueling air crew) my own credentials, are always interested in  aircraft since i was a young child, to the point i could tell what was flying over the house while i was inside. took one year of aeronautical engineerin, 7 years in the air force and still interested till this day. i haqve told people of this uccurance but they look at me if i'm nuts.
content.summary: I was aaeronautical engineering student ,and a postal employee also observed 1 mile away by other employees ,i was in traffic, got out of my jeep tried , observed no aircraft engines,tail,wings windows or noise

content.detailedDescription: I was on the back yard of the house, lay down on a hammock, see some planes passing, then start light object was coming in straight line from west to east staring at 35 degrees or 40 for about 2 minutes then went it was at 75 degree start slow down and make a 90 degrees turn to north 3second after 90 degrees east then make like a circle and stop then i see a disc shape object hovering in the same place, then an airplane came front south to north and the ufo start going straight up till disappear.  no plane do 90 degrees turn at that speed.

content.detailedDescription: I was taking a timelapse with my gopro hero4 black, i was testing settings while i aimed it at the blood moon event on september 27th. i captured several frames @ 10sec exposures with a constant interval. on only 1 of my frames i captured a glowing object which appears to traverse from the moon towards the camera exits the cameras frame and re-enters the frame, changes direction several times and appears to get larger or closer while doing so. we did not see the even live in action. it was upon review of the timelapse that we discovered the unusual light show. the time lapse was @ i believe 10sec intervals (possibly 15 secs) but i was pretty sure it was 10secs shutterspeeds. the sheer distance this object travels is amazing. please review the image i attached, i've been asking photgraphy experts if i may have accidently created this oddity, but i was reffered to submit this report because it appears i captured a "flight path"
content.summary: Object captured during timelapse leaving trail from moon.

content.detailedDescription: My boyfriend was looking outside and called for me to come look, i ran outside and there were two large circular fire ball looking lights in the sky, they darted around erratically and would glow very brightly then get dimmer. the second ball merged into the first one and it glowed very brightly and then dimmed and then looked as if it evaporated completely. i waited for a few minutes but it never came back and i saw nothing else in the sky. i saw a regular plane fly overhead maybe 5 minutes later and recognized that immediately. while watching the light i felt mezmerised and curious.
content.summary: 2 fireball like lights merged into each other then evaporated.

content.detailedDescription: I was at the university watching the blood moon. my attention got diverted as i was alone cold and bored so i looked the polite side of the moon. when i noticed a very large about 100ft size triangular plane flying southbound from where i was standing. when i first saw the object i thought it was and airplane but when i focused my eyes on the object i realized it was triangular and the lights were not set up as a regular plane. there was no blinking red light the passenger planes have and it was a matte black. so it easy blended with the night but the lights were bright . it moved in a linear direction and it was very large no where near the size of a drone. it didn't move erratically or any fdiffrently except that it was quicker than an airplane. my initial feeling when i realized it was nothing like a plane was to point it out to someone near me. i asked a girl sitting next to me and had to point it out to her since everyone was looking at the direction of the moon. she was shocked and confirmed my suspicioun that it was like nothing we have seen before. since i was taking photographs of the moon i had my ipad ready to photograph the ufo. i knew that without evidence i wouldn't be in denial of what i had seen. so i tried to snap pictures but it was too fast for the camera to focus and i couldn't see the details i saw with my naked eye to to the objects color blending in with the night. i got one picture that was decent-ish. i only got to take two pictures and it was gone. quickly i sent a skype message to my brother telling him that i saw what appeared to be a ufo. i lost sight of the object when a building got in the way as it traveled southward. i believe there were only 1 other witness other than myself because i didn't see anyone in the crowd of students looking bewildered or saying anything even though there were about 50 students there. they were all facing the moon which was east of me and the object was west of me on the opposite direction. the only other person who noticed was the girl whom i pointed it out to.
content.summary: Triangular object flown above university

content.detailedDescription: I was sitting on my back deck while watching the moon rise, it was approximately 8:05pm. i then saw a bright reddish orange light rising above the hill at the same area were the moon was rising. it appeared to be moving in a straight up direction, it was silent along with a small fire trail behind it as it was going in an upward direction, it then went in a north east direction. i wanted to yell out to my wife but i wasn't sure what it was. i then heard a plane engine as the light continued it was wobbling left to right and then it disappeared. i then observed a plane flying directly above me going in a easterly direction towards the rising moon. i then went into the house and told my wife what i had just witnessed. she told me that i should tell others of my experience and i told her that i wasn't going to share  this with anyone because they would think that i am crazy or doing drugs. i just cannot believe that i had just witnessed a ufo.
content.summary: Rose above hill as moon was rising, it was bright orange and red and changed direction, silent, changed direction and disapeared

content.detailedDescription:
Came out to witness blood moon event 30 minutes prior to eclipse peak. 

about 10-15 mins after peak, a bright star-like object was spotted east of the moon. i observed and assumed that it might be an unknown celestial body but soon realized that the object had not been seen before in the ~40 odd minutes that i've had my sights set skyward. 

object moved slightly the right and then shot upward toward the atmosphere until object was nearly too small to be seen by the naked eye. object was observed moving at a slower speed almost as if to mimic a man-made satellites orbit speed and distance and remained observable for several minutes before disappearing completely.

i was completely stunned as i'd never been witness to something of this nature before. i was in awe and terror.
content.summary: Ufo sighting witnessed during supermoon event

content.detailedDescription:
Myself and son(25) and daughter(27) where observing the bloodmoon from an empty parking lot. (although there was another couple also doing the same in the parking lot) just as the moon went total red, my daughter said hey, its; 11:11pm, and with in the couple minutes. my daughter shoutted, look a falling star, my son and i looked at what she was pointing to, a pale glowing object moving east to west. my thought was with in several seconds its going to burn up as it entered the atmosphere. just when i thought this would take place instead it turned 90* and shot straight up and outward into space. from my view it was going toward the red moon (east side). i lost track for a couple seconds and spotted it again on the west side of the moon heading downward with a zig zag motion, then a 90* turn shooting west again, i lost sight then.  
my thoughts were, this is no shooting star, they don't change course at a 90* angle and this was no plane traveling at a speed that to me would be like a slow moving shooting star. it was quite exciting, when we all realized, there is absolutely nothing here on earth that could do what that object just did, and then to think we just saw a ufo for real! wow, amazing. my son then walked over to the other couple in the parking lot to ask if they saw what we just saw, they too confirmed they had seen it and there was no way anything earthly could move like it did and at that speed.
content.summary: East/west travel then 90* turn up and out of view, back into view downward then 90* turn west, zig zag pattern then disappeared, at time of blood moon

content.detailedDescription: It was about 2:oo am.  i was getting a drink of water and looked out the window of my kitchen.  the sky was clear. no clouds.  it was a summer night.  i saw what i believed to be a helicopter because it wasn't that far from my house and i saw pulsating lights that changed colors (red, blue, green, white).  it hovered but made no sound.  i went back to watching a favorite movie of mine (mad max).  it ended at around 4:00 am and when i looked out the window, the star-like object was still hovering but a little further away.  i decided to get my binoculars and when i looked through them i saw what almost looked like a laser pointer in the sky that changed colors rapidly (red, blue, green, white) and made all different shapes.  i could not see an actual object or craft associated with the pulsating lights but nonetheless it felt weird and i had never in my life seen this object before (and i do a lot of star gazing).  it is now september of 2015 and there are now three of the same objects in the sky (ne) and four in the sky, across from my house (western sky).  they all look identical and all have the same pulsating colors and often, they will move horizontally in a super fast burst and then return to their original location in the sky.  they have never moved up or down, just left to right or right to left.  i have no idea what they are but my wife and neighbor have looked at them and also agree that they have never in their lives seen these star-like objects.
content.summary: Pulsating lights (red, blue, green, white) from a star-like object never before seen in the sky.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving south on i-95 just before the baltimore tunnels.  about 20 minutes before the tunnels i observed a craft flying but stationary off to my left.  the craft had no wings but looked a little like a blimp.  i thought it very high for a blimp like the goodyear ones.  the craft remained totally stationary not moving up or down. i saw no wings or any other flight control devices.  i am a navy veteran who was involved in naval aviation.  i later obtained my private pilot license.  i know a bit about aviation.  i was not sure if this craft was something the military testing grounds launched. the object was totally stationer and did not move or bob like a blimp would at that altitude. i just felt strange there were no military aircraft looking to see this object.  if you can tell me it is a device being tested by the military i'll be satisfied.  if not, you need to look into this.  was weapons testing a new product or what.  i thought the object may be tethered but i saw no cable of any kind from my position. the whole thing seemed so strange to me at the time.  the sun was up but there was no reflection off the craft to indicate sunlight.  it's color appeared white. i could not stop the car to take a picture.  i just would like an answer.  the object appeared to me to be about 1,000 to 2,000 agl.  i hope someone will give you an answer.  just the strangest thing i'd ever seen.  feel free to contact me at 609-647-7755
content.summary: Just observed while driving south on i-95 heading to the tunnels of baltimore

content.detailedDescription:
Where were you and what were you doing at the time?
-i was in my living room next to our balcony occasionally going out out to peak at the super blood moon lunar eclipse.

what made you first notice the object?
-on one of the occasions when i stepped out i looked up towards the moon and immediately noticed a bright object silently moving across the sky. i was awestruck but then went into an excited state when it completely stopped at a single point in the sky; that's when i called for my wife. 

what did you think object was when you first noticed it?
-honestly i had no idea, i thought maybe it could have been a helicopter at first; however, when it stopped and hovered my helicopter theory kinda wen't out the window. the entire time it was silent, all you could hear are crickets and some cars. i grew up in the l.A. area was used to helicopters, even the ones that had silencing capabilities; those still made a noticeable sound. this object made no sound at all.

describe the object and its actions and motions in detail.
-i had a pair of binoculars and managed to look it at briefly when it paused in the sky. it had two bright lights alternating green and then red. the light could be seen reflected off only the bottom part of the object. the surface where the light illuminated seemed similar to diamond plated pattern sheet metal. 

-as far as it's movement; the first time i saw it was coming from the direction of the mcdowell mountains heading east to west stopping and pausing briefly in the sky. the movement was pretty linear the first time. after my wife and i wen't back inside thinking it was gone, i wen't back out again. that's when it returned and was heading west to east, my camera did not pick up great detail and the video is shaky because of how zoomed in i was but at one point it was right next to the blood colored moon aprox at 44 seconds in, almost as if it was observing it. it zig zagged a few times in way that would not make sense for any helicopter to to and all while pulsating alternating green and red, it made its way behind the mcdowell mountains and turned a solid red, that is when my camera had trouble picking it up. it stopped in placed and descended directly behind the mountains while glowing a bright red. 

describe your feelings, reactions and actions during and after sighting the object.
-i was excited, scared a bit, but overall in absolute wonder. now i am saying this was a ufo as in unidentified flying object. it could be military, a massive drone, or an actual thing out of this world i don't know. all i know is that it was an amazing sight and definitely not what you see every night in the night sky.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Bright flashing red and green object, paused in middle of sky, came back and zigzagged by red colored lunar eclipse.

content.detailedDescription: Brother was looking to the northwest at what was thought was the sun! looked a little to the left and realized that that was the sun! looked back at original bright light and wondered what could be so bright as to be mistaken as the sun! there was a considerable gap between the sun and the other bright light! took a bunch of pictures and went home! a few days later enlarged and enhanced the pictures and began to see bright glowing sphere with what looked like sparkles inside! there is a pict with an airplane in view! also there is another object that can't quite be made out! have never seen objects like this before! got pictures that i will tyr to upload!
content.summary: Looking at what was thought was the sun! wasn't! bright light observed! didn't see a sphere until days later when pict was enlarged!

content.detailedDescription:
My son and i were leaving our house on sunday september 27th at 10:30 am to get breakfast. a flashing light caught my eye as i looked at the sky. i assumed it was mylar balloons someone accidently set free from dillons but i told my son to get our binoculars. he couldn't find them so i left him to watch and i got them. focused on the object and what i saw was gold and blue flashing around in a counterclockwise
fashion. the brightest edge was on its east side but it was in the northern sky slowly heading east. it started to leave our view behind trees and my son and i looked back and the was another object from where the first one was but it had a
very bright light flashing three times repeatedly. my son and i took turns looking through the binoculars and i said it's cylindrical and he replied it's pill shaped. now we were in shock enough about that but then the first object came back at the same altitude as the pill shaped craft. the first craft approached the second one and as they got close all of a sudden the circled eachother once and the first craft then proceeded north out of sight. now we were in trouble because it's now 11:00 am and my wife wanted breakfast. she did come out and see the first bright light but did not use binoculars. my son also had a football game so we were late. we left while the pill shaped craft was in the air and it was still there when we got back at 11:15 am. i sent him in to eat but he and i had to finish the sighting. i proceeded to watch as it slowly headed south overhead but it also gained altitude and went out of sight. during our sighting we also watched four white commercial airplanes pass at a lower altitude while both object were in sight. i was always open to there being ufos but after this both my son and i know it's true! amazing. i've never seen anything like that in my life and probably never will again but i'll be watching.
content.summary: Daytime sighting with two objects. one rotating and the other pill shaped with one fladhing light.

content.detailedDescription: watching the blood moon eclipse, i notice an object of multiple colors, static and hoovering in the sky as planes will pass by. in the video, as you can see the lights of this ufo change from reddish to green and yellowish color. at the beginning of the video, you can see that a plane is passing by at the bottom of the screen and the ufo is just hoovering above, completely static. after a few seconds this ufo descends vertically at high speed (way faster that the plane you see passing by at the beginning of the video) till probably lands somewhere behind some trees.By the way the object is of triangular shape which can be seen better in other video i got of the same object....This was not a plane...
content.summary: Watching blood moon eclipse

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i kept going outside to see the different phases of the eclipse last night (sept. 27 2015) we saw that high above the moon was a very bright object. very very bright, we thought maybe it was a planet or star or something like that. then we realized it looked like it was reflecting the light of the moon. over 20-25 minutes it descended and then was just gone. i took several pictures of it with my cell phone. we have a friend in colorado who was also watching the eclipse and he didn't see anything in the sky like what we saw. at first i assumed it was some natural phenomenon but the more we watched the less it looked like anything else i have ever seen in the sky. looking back at the pictures i still can't be sure what it is, that is why i am filing this report. we looked outside every few minutes, it kept getting lower and lower...Seemingly closer to the moon and then it disappeared. i made a collage photo of some of the different elevations...The third pic in the collage is just a cropped version of one of the others. i have several pics on my phone if you would like anymore. i added one of the single pictures, currently having trouble uploading the rest...But i have them and can send later if you want them
content.summary: Watching eclipse, noticed object above moon, mins later it was lower, mins later gone

content.detailedDescription: I saw something off in the distance it looked like a star as i watched i called my fiance to come look i thought it was the comet that was supposepd to hit earth as it got closer the lights dim and changed pattern and i could see a distinct triangular body to the craft and lights on the outside moving and lighting different colors it hovered for a while then it disappeared i didnt see it fly off it was just gone

content.detailedDescription:
Camped on beatty's butte east of hart mountain national antelope refuge while on an offroad motorcycle tour. we were just going to bed when an extremely bright white light appeared in the western sky as if an aircraft with landing lights was flying directly towards us. no sound was heard for the duration of the sighting. suddenly, one at a time, bright orange lights dropped out the area where the bright light had been. the orange lights faded away almost immediately, much faster than a typical flare drop from a military aircraft and much brighter. the same image suddenly appeared north west of the initial sighting. the same bright white light with orange lights dropping out of it happened. the same series of lights appeared again where the original craft had been and one more time to the northwest. 

creepy was the word we both used to describe the sighting as there was no sound and the lights, if known military would have been audible. we did not have a fire or any other indication that we were camped out there but we have been through this country many times and witnessed low flying military aircraft presumably from the kingsley air national guard base in klamath falls, or. the area is also known as the catlow valley and is some of the most remote uninhabited parts of the lower forty eight states just north of the nevada border.

we would very much like to know if there was any military training going on in the area at that time.
content.summary: Very bright white light that either hovered or was travelling directly at viewers just below big dipper

content.detailedDescription:
I and a group of people from my neighborhood were gathered at a street corner in an attempt to view the sept. 28 lunar eclipse and "blood moon" event. we saw the lunar disc disappear and waited several moments for the
next phase, but after about 20 minutes with nothing much happening, compounded by high clouds, all my companions departed. i remained hoping to see the lunar disc return, but then noticed, in the darkness sky, a strange, faint cloud grouping almost directly across my viewing position and seemingly positioned above a house chimney. i could just make up strange angles vary dissimilar from the other basically horizontal cloud formations.Using my samsung android note ii cellphone i took several photos. within a few minutes the "cloud formation" had dissolved.

then when looking at the cellphone photos, it revealed a more detailed
image including those that also showed a sharp beam of light seemingly emitted from the tip of the rocket shaped central body and a pair of
what looked very much like large whale flippers protruding from its sides. there were no sounds heard. since distance was unknown, size was also unknown, though the impression was of large dimensions.

many years ago i was a mufon field investigator and had
witnessed some anomalous events while serving in that function. i had not
witness anything of this nature for quite some time. my objective impression was that it could be some compilation/visual trick of cloud and light interactions, but my subjective impression was otherwise...
an anomaly of unusual proportions on several levels and certainly a
pleasure to experience.
content.summary: While observing lunar eclipse, i know a strange cloud form and using my cellphone took photos.

content.detailedDescription: When watching this display, i thought it would be all over the front page of everynewspaper on vancouver island. for some reason i told myself to always remember this unbelievable experiance, and it was. there was a pulsing almost a heartbeat i could feel coming from this craft. i felt as if it was aware of me , perhaps because it did not only change direction but came towards the highway in a blink of a eye. i watched this while diving a 75 vw beetle and was the only person on the malahat highway while this went on, obviously this car had little to no electronics , i dont know if that meens anything, the cars performance was not effected. i watched the display of changing directions for about 1-2 minutes but it sure seemed longer at the time. as said before by other folks, it took off like the strship on startrack the tail end of light catching up to it and just gone... it was the most incredable experiance i have felt and seen with its leaving of our planet... this was many years ago, this was a experiance that was important to me, there is no way this was from earth and no mistake for my experiance, incidentually, iam not sure if this is related but, shortly after i had a dream and in this dream i remember part of it seeing colors in the sky, the incrediable thing was.. i have never seen these colors on earth before, i can really even discribe them and while dreaming i was even saying that to myself how amazing the colors were and i have never seen them...I could ad more, but, ill leave this for now... i have only discussed this with 3-4 people in over 30 years, i just thought to share with you as you may have so many challanges.. i have no doubt, we all will be believes soon.
content.summary: See description below

content.detailedDescription:
On 9/11, i was out with the puppy, taking him out to pee, it was a bit after 5:30am, but before 6:00am, and i saw this strange light just hovering to the west.  i called to my husband to grab my cell phone and i managed to get three images before it flew off.

i managed to get three images.  (i'm unable to remove the personal information from them, so i will not send them to you.)

there was a thick, black storm cloud cover that was opaque for as far as the eye could see, so it wasn't a break in the cloud cover showing a star shining through.  when i realized it wasn't a star shining through the thickness of the cloud, that's when i yelled for my phone and snapped pics.  

i'm not really sure of possible distances because of the opaque cloud cover.

there was no lightning or anything atmospheric like that going on at the time, either.

at first, it looked like one big, bright light.  then it separated into two.  i thought the third pic was still of the two lights, but when enlarged, it shows a smaller triangle at what i guess is the front with three lights more than the other two images.  

it moved off pretty quickly.

i knew i'd seen something which i couldn't easily identify, as far as it wasn't a plane or helicopter.  i was glad i was able to get three pictures of whatever it was, even if i'm not adept enough with my phone to have gotten an actual recording as opposed to images.

btw, this was in the bixby, oklahoma area.  

thank you.
content.summary: Saw a light that wasn't backlit against the cloud cover.  realized it was hovering and asked the husband for my phone to take pics.

content.detailedDescription:
Driving home after dinner with wife and baby... time was 8:40pm and while driving north on ca 133 from laguna beach ca to irvine ca (quail hill) area,  noticed a massive v shaped cloud over a what appears to be a very large area of southern orange county.

my wife took several photos of which one has been included.  i had to adjust lighting/contrast to get the v to become visible.  the photo was taken with an iphone and because it was dark outside, it is not too clear.

i observed the cloud for about an hour as it was stationery.  both sides of the v were identical in length and in thickness.  the "cloud" seemed to be separated from surrounding clouds by a clear margin all the way around, as if the v was pushing aside all other cloud. 

during the hour that i was watching the "v", the low level clouds around it would change shape, move away, dissipate and do normal cloud things, except the "v" always stood still and always managed to maintain a margin of clear sky around it.

i was getting tired and went to bed.  around 9:45.
content.summary: Massive v shaped cloud standing apart from all other clouds for over 1 hour

content.detailedDescription: I was near my house at a forestroute, walking the dogs. i was looking up to the skies hoping to see something, and i got more than i had hoped for. at first it looked like a regular star, but then i saw it started moving. it was moving a lot faster than a satellite, to the left. then it turned and flew down/left. i was in awe, almost paralyzed. it was so amazing. after flying there for about three minutes, the light faded away, and i didn't see it again.
content.summary: It looked like a moving star, it made directional changes.
